I vote we
add an .isort.cfg file drop .flake8 and .pylintrc since we're adopting black In the proposed .isort.cfg , I'd put [settings] ; black-compatible options, ref https://pycqa.github.io/isort/docs/configuration/profiles.html#black (20 more lines were trimmed) (the isort options are defined here) I'm happy to be outvoted on any particular style point, but I think we should take the opportunity to choose the style options we want before we do the big black + isort run. (Also, I think we'll need to do a little manual checking of quirks that arise from that style-run before we merge the changes in, like if the first import gets moved down in a file with a license notice comment, the last section of license notice comment is going to be attached to that import lower in the file instead of staying above all the code) I'm so excited to tidy up this whole codebase. Thanks for setting up the hooks!
